    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="PTM3.4.10">
<l>ceṅkamalat tayaṉaṉaiya maṟaiyōr kāḻic cīrāma viṇṇakareṉ ceṅkaṇ mālai</l>
<l>yaṅkamalat taṭavayalcū ḻāli nāṭa ṉaruḷmāri yaraṭṭamukki yaṭaiyār cīyam</l>
<l>koṅkumalar kuḻaliyarvēḷ maṅkai vēntaṉ koṟṟavēl parakālaṉ kaliyaṉ coṉṉa</l>
<l>caṅkamukat tamiḻmālai pattum vallār taṭaṅkaṭalcū ḻulakukkut talaivar tāmē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>Those who master the ten [verses] of this garland in the Tamil</l>
<l rend="indent">by which the assembly is pleased,</l>
<l>About my bright-eyed Māl of Cīrāmaviṇṇakaram in Kāḻi with Vedic experts</l>
<l rend="indent">who are like [Brahmā,] the Unborn on the red lotus,</l>
<l>Composed by Kaliyaṉ, Parakālaṉ with the victory spear, the king of Maṅkai,</l>
<l rend="indent">the desire of those in whose curls are honey-laden buds,</l>
<l>A lion to his enemies, crushing their arrogance, a shower of mercy,</l>
<l rend="indent">lord of Ālināṭu encircled by wide fields with  fine lotuses,</l>
<l rend="indent">they will be leaders of earth encircled by the wide sea.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
